// The user loads the page with a GET request //

sequenceDiagram
    participant User
    participant browser
    participant server

// THE BROWSER MAKES A GET REQUEST TO THE SERVER, WHICH RESPONDS WITH AN HTML DOCUMENT //

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/notes
    activate server
    server-->>browser: HTML document
    deactivate server

// THE BROWSER MAKES A GET REQUEST TO THE SERVER, WHICH RESPONDS WITH A CSS FILE //

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.css
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the css file
    deactivate server

// THE BROWSER MAKES A GET REQUEST TO THE SERVER, WHICH RESPONDS WITH A JAVASCRIPT FILE //

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/main.js
    activate server
    server-->>browser: the JavaScript file
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser starts executing the JavaScript code that fetches the JSON from the server

    browser->>server: GET https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/data.json
    activate server
    server-->>browser: [{ "content": "f", "date": "2024-02-02T10:01:30.454Z" }, ... ]
    deactivate server

    Note right of browser: The browser executes the callback function that renders the notes

// THE USER CLICKS ON THE TEXTBOX, ENTERS INFORMATION, AND CLICKS SAVE //

    User->>Browser: Makes a POST request to /new_note
    Browser->>Server: POST /new_note

    Server-->>Browser: Response 302 Found
    Server-->>Browser: Location: /exampleapp/notes

    Browser->>User: Redirects to /exampleapp/notes

